<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1207,1554]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,331,1327,1353]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Comment:</emphasis>
According to a catalogue entry by Peters this specimen is an original exemplar of Tomes description. ZMB 3033 agrees with locality, collector and the exact collecting date in Tomes’ description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dobson, G. E." box="[151,387,1408,1434]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="382 - 388" refId="ref44843" refString="Dobson, G. E. (1875) On the genus Chalinolobus, with descriptions of new or little-known species. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1875, 382 - 388." type="journal article" year="1875">Dobson (1875: 388)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the “type” is in 
<collectingRegion box="[762,839,1408,1434]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Berlin</collectingRegion>
. O. Thomas considered that 
<specimenCount box="[1174,1347,1408,1434]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
he saw in the Tomes collection matched the measurements given in Tomes’ original description (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, O." pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="77 - 83" refId="ref47999" refString="Thomas, O. (1905) New African Mammals of the Genera Glauconycteris, Lutra, Funisciurus, Arvicanthis, Lophiomys, and Procavia. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 15, 77 - 83." type="journal article" year="1905">Thomas 1905: 77</bibRefCitation>
). Tomes did not specify the number of specimens he examined, hence we consider ZMB 3033 as well as the both specimens ex coll. Tomes (= BMNH 1907.1.1.437–438 skins and skulls) as 
<typeStatus box="[1144,1250,1528,1554]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">syntypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
